___version.description: File version (always the first entry in the object) and must be a positive integer.

___sourceRoot.default: An optional source root, useful for relocating source files on a server or removing repeated values in the 'sources' entry.  This value is prepended to the individual entries in the 'source' field.

___sources.description: A list of original sources used by the 'mappings' entry.

___file.default: An optional name of the generated code that this source map is associated with.

___names.description: A list of symbol names used by the 'mappings' entry.

___sourcesContent.description: An optional list of source content, useful when the 'source' can�t be hosted. The contents are listed in the same order as the sources in line 5. 'null' may be used if some original sources should be retrieved by name.

___mappings.description: A string with the encoded mapping data.
